    facts: ["Most of Kornati National Park's 89 islands are privately owned by Murter islanders","Murter islanders commute by boat to tend olive trees on uninhabited Kornati islands","Kornati is the densest archipelago in the Mediterranean — 89 islands in a small area","The National Park protects Kornati while allowing traditional use","Murter serves as the gateway to Kornati National Park, where the islanders tend their olive trees by boat."],
    vocab: [{"hr":"maslina","en":"olive tree","note":"Kornatski maslinici (Kornati olive groves) are tended by Murter islanders — ancient trees on bare limestone islands"},{"hr":"arhipelag","en":"archipelago","note":"Kornati arhipelag has 89 islands — the densest archipelago in the Mediterranean, all within sight of each other"},{"hr":"Murterin","en":"person from Murter","note":"The Murterini own most of the uninhabited islands in the Kornati archipelago."}],
