    tagline: "Diocletian's Palace — A Living Roman City",
    intro: "Split is Croatia's second-largest city and the cultural capital of Dalmatia — built inside, around, and on top of the 1,700-year-old Roman palace of Emperor Diocletian. Two hundred thousand people live in a city whose historic core IS the palace, a UNESCO World Heritage site where laundry hangs over Roman columns and cafés operate inside imperial halls.",
    history: "Diocletian, the Roman emperor born in nearby Salona, built his retirement palace here in 305 AD — a vast fortified complex by the sea. After the fall of Rome and the destruction of Salona by Avars and Slavs around 614 AD, refugees moved into the abandoned palace and have lived there continuously ever since — making Split's old town the world's only inhabited Roman imperial palace. Through Byzantine, Venetian, Habsburg, and Yugoslav rule, the palace stones absorbed each civilisation's adaptations. The Riva promenade and the open-air bell tower of Saint Domnius are the city's icons.",
    facts: ["Split is the only city in the world built inside a Roman imperial palace — Diocletian's Palace is still the living heart of the city","The Cathedral of Saint Domnius (built into Diocletian's mausoleum) is one of the oldest active Catholic cathedrals in the world — using Roman structures since the 7th century","Hajduk Split, founded in 1911 in a Prague café by Split students, is one of Croatia's two giant football clubs — fanatical Torcida supporters define the Split identity","Marjan Hill, the wooded peninsula behind the city, is Split's 'lungs' — locals call it the 'pluća grada' (lungs of the city)","Split was the most-filmed location in Croatia for Game of Thrones — Diocletian's cellars served as the dragon dungeons of Meereen"],
    vocab: [{"hr":"Splićanin","en":"person from Split","note":"Splićanin (m) / Splićanka (f) — Split people are famously direct, ironic, and intensely proud of their city and Hajduk"},{"hr":"Riva","en":"the seafront promenade","note":"Split's Riva is THE social space — afternoon and evening strolls (špica) on the Riva are non-negotiable"},{"hr":"Torcida","en":"Hajduk's ultras","note":"Founded 1950 — the oldest organised supporters group in Europe. Torcida defines Split's football culture"}],
    didYouKnow: "Diocletian's Palace covers 38,700 m² — the size of about five football pitches — and contains more than 220 separate buildings within the original Roman walls.",
