    intro: "Milna is a small harbour town on the western tip of Brač, set in a deeply protected bay that has been one of the most reliable sailing refuges on the Adriatic since antiquity. Cypress-lined coves, 18th-century baroque architecture, and the Cerinić family's monumental parish church define Milna's character.",
