    facts: ["Milna's harbour is one of the most sheltered on the central Dalmatian coast — protected from all wind directions","Napoleon's fleet anchored at Milna in 1806–07 during the French Illyrian period","The baroque parish church of the Annunciation (1783) holds Croatia's largest island church organ","Milna was the home harbour of the 19th-century Brač sailing fleet — captains and ship-owners built mansions here","Three of Brač's six summer Renaissance villas are in or near Milna — Cerinić, Marčić, Slokić"],
