    intro: "Veliko Trgovišće is a Zagorje municipality in Krapina-Zagorje County, west of Zabok, best known as the birthplace in 1922 of Franjo Tuđman — the historian, general, and politician who served as the first President of independent Croatia from 1990 until his death in 1999. The Tuđman family house in the village is preserved as a memorial site.",
    history: "Veliko Trgovišće was historically a Kajkavian-speaking Zagorje market village. Franjo Tuđman was born here on 14 May 1922. After serving as a Partisan during the Second World War, he later became a historian, was imprisoned twice in Yugoslavia for his political views, founded the Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) in 1989, and led Croatia to independence in 1991. He was elected president three times and died in office on 10 December 1999. The Veliko Trgovišće birthplace is preserved as the Tuđman Memorial Home, and the family is buried in the nearby village cemetery.",
    facts: ["Franjo Tuđman, first President of independent Croatia, was born in Veliko Trgovišće on 14 May 1922","The Tuđman birth house (Spomen dom Franje Tuđmana) is preserved as a memorial site in the village","Veliko Trgovišće is a Kajkavian-speaking Zagorje village west of Zabok in Krapina-Zagorje County","Tuđman is buried at Mirogoj cemetery in Zagreb, but family members are interred in the local Veliko Trgovišće cemetery","The municipality includes the villages of Družilovec, Jezero Klanječko, and Vižovlje"],
