    history: "Belica developed as a small Hungarian Zala County village until 1918, and since then has been part of Croatia. Like all Lower Međimurje villages, its character has been shaped by intensive lowland farming on the flat alluvial soils between the Mura and Drava. The municipality is part of the wider Lower Međimurje (Donje Međimurje) region centred on Prelog.",
    facts: ["Belica lies in the flat Lower Međimurje plain south of Čakovec, between the Mura and Drava rivers","The area is intensively farmed for grain, maize, and vegetables on rich alluvial soil","Belica is part of Međimurje County, the smallest and most densely populated county in Croatia","Like all Međimurje, Belica was part of Hungarian Zala County until 1918","Belica sits on the flat alluvial soils between the Mura and Drava, within the Lower Međimurje region centred on Prelog."],
