    intro: "Šenkovec is a small Međimurje municipality on the immediate western edge of Čakovec, known historically as the burial site of the Zrinski family — Croatia's most famous noble dynasty, who held Međimurje as their family estate for nearly two centuries. The Pauline monastery church of Saint Helen in Šenkovec contains Zrinski tombs.",
    history: "The Pauline monastery and church of Saint Helen at Šenkovec was the family church and burial site of the Zrinski family from the 16th century, when they acquired Međimurje. Several Zrinski counts, including Nikola IV Zrinski (the Hero of Siget, who died defending Szigetvár against the Ottomans in 1566) and Nikola VII Zrinski, are connected to the site. The 1671 execution of Petar Zrinski and Fran Krsto Frankopan for their conspiracy against the Habsburgs effectively ended the dynasty, and the Habsburgs confiscated the Šenkovec estate. The Pauline order was dissolved in 1786 by Joseph II.",
    facts: ["The Pauline church of Saint Helen in Šenkovec was the burial church of the Zrinski family, lords of Međimurje","Nikola IV Zrinski, the Hero of Siget who died defending Szigetvár in 1566, is connected to the Zrinski Šenkovec burial site","The Zrinski dynasty ended after Petar Zrinski's execution in Wiener Neustadt on 30 April 1671 for conspiracy against the Habsburgs","The Pauline monastery at Šenkovec was dissolved in 1786 by Habsburg emperor Joseph II","Šenkovec lies immediately west of Čakovec in Međimurje County"],
    vocab: [{"hr":"Zrinski","en":"the Zrinski noble family","note":"Šenkovec was the Zrinski family burial church — the lords of Međimurje"},{"hr":"pavlini","en":"Paulines (Order of Saint Paul)","note":"Pavlinski samostan — Pauline monastery — stood at Šenkovec from the 16th century until 1786"},{"hr":"grobnica","en":"tomb / crypt","note":"Zrinska grobnica — the Zrinski tombs were at the Šenkovec Pauline church"}],
