    history: "The Keglević family, one of the most prominent Croatian noble houses, held lands around Sveti Križ Začretje from the 16th century. Their castle in Začretje was rebuilt in the 18th century in baroque style. The parish church of the Holy Cross developed as a regional pilgrimage site, with a venerated cross. Like all Zagorje villages, the area was Kajkavian-speaking peasant country under Habsburg administration; the dissolution of feudalism in 1848 transformed the economy.",
