    facts: ["Oprtalj's surviving Venetian-era loggia and town walls date principally to the 15th–17th centuries","The town was under the Republic of Venice from 1421 to 1797","Oprtalj is officially bilingual Croatian-Italian under Istria County's statutes","The parish church of Saint George (Sveti Juraj) sits at the highest point of the town","Oprtalj sits on a ridge with views across the Mirna valley toward Motovun on the next ridge to the south"],
