    history: "Mošćenice was settled by the Liburnians (an Illyrian tribe) in pre-Roman times, on a defensive hilltop position above the sea. Under Rome, then Byzantium, then medieval Croatian and Habsburg rulers, it remained a fortified village. From the 15th century it was part of the Habsburg holdings under the Counts of Pazin and Rijeka, and was administered by the Walsee family and later directly by Austria. The walled core, narrow lanes, and small parish church of Saint Andrew survive substantially intact. Today Mošćenice and the coastal Mošćenička Draga together form a single municipality.",
