    history: "Hreljin and its castle were the seat of one of the eight municipalities (kotari) named in the 1288 Vinodol Statute, the law code given by the Frankopan family to their Vinodol subjects. The hilltop position controlled the upper Vinodol valley and the route inland toward Gorski Kotar. Under the Frankopans and later the Habsburgs, the castle remained a regional centre; it fell into ruin after the early modern period, but the stone shell of Hreljingrad survives. The village below was reduced significantly in population over the 20th century as residents moved to coastal Kraljevica and Bakar, but Hreljin remains the seat of a small parish.",
