    didYouKnow: "The griffon vultures of Beli are so closely tied to traditional sheep farming on Cres that the birds nearly went extinct in the 20th century when subsistence shepherding declined — they depend on carrion from outdoor-grazing sheep, and Beli's conservation programme has had to combine bird protection with support for the island's traditional shepherds.",
