    history: "Kaštel Štafilić was founded in 1500 by the Trogir patrician Stjepan Štafilić (Stafileo), who built a fortified tower as the seat of his estate against Ottoman raids. As with the other six Kaštela, the village grew around the tower with dense stone houses for the tenant farmers brought down from Kozjak. The Stafileo family, later prominent at the Venetian court, also produced Giovanni Stafileo, papal nuncio to Henry VIII of England. In the 20th century Split airport (Resnik) was built on the plain west of the village, making Kaštel Štafilić the air gateway to central Dalmatia.",
    facts: ["Kaštel Štafilić was founded around 1500 by Stjepan Štafilić of Trogir, builder of the fortified tower","The Stari Maslina olive at Kaštel Štafilić is certified at over 1,500 years old — the oldest documented olive in Croatia","It is the westernmost of the seven Kaštela settlements, bordering Trogir municipality","Split airport (Resnik) sits in the territory of Kaštel Štafilić","Papal diplomat Giovanni Stafileo, nuncio to Henry VIII, came from this Trogir noble family"],
