    history: "Brist appears in late-medieval Bosnian and Venetian documents as a small Croat settlement on the southern Makarska Riviera, populated by farmers and fishermen. The most famous son of Brist, Andrija Kačić Miošić, was born here in 1704, entered the Franciscan order, and later moved to the monastery at neighbouring Zaostrog where he wrote his celebrated Razgovor ugodni naroda slovinskoga. A monument to Kačić Miošić stands in the village. Today Brist remains a small coastal village with a modest tourism sector and continued recognition as Kačić Miošić's birthplace.",
