    history: "Komarna was historically a small settlement of farmers and fishermen on the southern Dalmatian coast, opposite the western end of the Pelješac peninsula. Its strategic importance grew in the late 20th century when the Croatian government planned a bridge to bypass the short Bosnian-Herzegovinian access to the sea at Neum, eliminating the need for border crossings on the road to Dubrovnik. The Pelješac Bridge, 2.4 km long, opened on 26 July 2022, with Komarna as its mainland anchor. The settlement now lives largely in the shadow of the bridge.",
