    didYouKnow: "The Konavle dialect preserves several archaic Slavic linguistic features lost in standard Croatian, and the Republic of Ragusa maintained a distinct local administration over Konavle for nearly 400 years until the Republic itself was abolished by Napoleon in 1808.",
